### PHP Multidimensional Arrays

A multidimensional array is an array that contains one or more arrays.

### Creating Multidimensional Arrays

```php
<?php
// 2D indexed array
$matrix = [
    [1, 2, 3],
    [4, 5, 6],
    [7, 8, 9]
];

// Array of associative arrays
$users = [
    ["name" => "Alice", "email" => "alice@example.com"],
    ["name" => "Bob", "email" => "bob@example.com"],
    ["name" => "Charlie", "email" => "charlie@example.com"]
];
?>
```

### Accessing Elements

```php
<?php
$matrix = [
    [1, 2, 3],
    [4, 5, 6],
    [7, 8, 9]
];

echo $matrix[0][0]; // 1 (first row, first col)
echo $matrix[1][2]; // 6 (second row, third col)

// Loop through
for ($row = 0; $row < count($matrix); $row++) {
    for ($col = 0; $col < count($matrix[$row]); $col++) {
        echo $matrix[$row][$col] . " ";
    }
    echo "<br>";
}
?>
```

### Nested foreach

```php
<?php
foreach ($users as $user) {
    foreach ($user as $key => $value) {
        echo "$key: $value<br>";
    }
    echo "---<br>";
}
?>
```

> **Key Point:** Multidimensional arrays are useful for representing tables, matrices, or collections of complex records.
